    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "SOUTHWEST\nJULY 6, 2004 FLIGHT SCHEDULE\nAs a Senior Attorney,\nI'm happy to provide\nlegal assistance to\nour departments.",
      "Pacific\ncentra\nEastern\nDeton Mages Fail\nReno/ Tanoe\n(San Francisco Area\n(San Francisco Area\nLas vega:\nLos Al\n(LAX) Orange\nsan Dieg\n(Palm Springs Area\nSalt Lake City\nAmarillo\nLubbock\nKansas City\nSt. Louis\nTulsa\nOklahoma City Little Rock\nNashville\nEl Paso\nSan Antonio\nChrist\nHarlingen/South Padre Island\nNew Orleans\nTamy\nNew nonstop service starts July 6, 2004.\nNew nonstop service starts August 8, 2004.\nIndianapolis, Phoenix, and Tucson do not observe daylight-saving time.\nManchester)\n(Biston Area)\nton (BWI)\n(D.C. Area)\nuthern virginia,\nRaleigh-Durham (RDU)\nWest Palm Beach\nMiami erdale\nVisit us at southwest.com® for an up-to-date\nflight schedule.\nYou can now check in for your flight and print\nyour boarding pass at southwest.com or at\nthe Southwest Skycap,* Ticket Counter,\nRAPID CHECK-IN Kiosk, or at your gate at\nleast one hour prior to departure. (20 minutes\nprior to scheduled departure, boarding pass\ndistribution is available at the Departure\nGate only.)\nCargo Customers, mail requests to:\nCargo Customer Schedule List, HDQ/3CM,\nP.O. Box 36611, Dallas, TX 75235-1611.\nAll other correspondence should be sent to:\nSouthwest Airlines Co.,\nP.O. Box 36611, Dallas, TX 75235-1611.\n*Where available\nSOUTHWEST"
